{"lemma":"طُهْرُ","slug":"طُهْرُ","root":"ط.ه.ر","root_slug":"ط-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طُهْرُ","root":"طهر","pos":"V","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27212","n27215","n27216"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8F%D9%87%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become pure"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to purify"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to circumcise"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ط ه ر (ṭ h r). Cognate with Biblical Hebrew טהר (taher, “to be clean, to be pure”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27212","headword_ar":"طَهَرَ","root":"Thr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) aor. of each"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TahaArapN","text_ar":"طَهَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) which is of each verb, (S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuhorN","text_ar":"طُهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, K,) or the latter is a simple subst., (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, clean, free from dirt"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * Msb, K. *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ThArp","text_ar":"طهارة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of two kinds; [properly] corporeal and [tropically] spiritual. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taharato","text_ar":"طَهَرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taharato mina AlHayoDi","text_ar":"طَهَرَتْ مِنَ الحَيْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahurato","text_ar":"طَهُرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) which is allowable, (IAar,) but of rare occurrence, (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahirato","text_ar":"طَهِرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is of more rare occurrence;] (M, El-Isnawee;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuhorN","text_ar":"طُهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TahaArapN","text_ar":"طَهَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuhuwrN","text_ar":"طُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TahuwrN","text_ar":"طَهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, pure from the menstrual discharge;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her discharge of blood stopped."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K.) See also 5. The saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Al$~aApa taqo*iY Ea$orFA vum~a taTohuru","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الشَّاةَ تَقْذِى عَشْرًا ثُمَّ تَطْهُرُ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1887},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the ewe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-goat, emits a white fluid from her womb during ten"},{"kind":"text","text":"nights,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then becomes pure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is mentioned on the authority of Lh: but ISd says, whether he mentioned this as heard from the Arabs, or did so presumptuously, I know not. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taharahu","text_ar":"طَهَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TahorN","text_ar":"طَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) (TK,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused it, to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become, distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remote;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboEadahu","text_ar":"اَبْعَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaHarahu","text_ar":"طَحَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"being substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","Sb","M","Mgh","IAar","TK","O"]},{"entry_id":"n27215","headword_ar":"طُهْرٌ","root":"Thr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[see 1: ―         -b2- ]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Cleanness; freedom from dirt"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pureness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of pureness from the menstrual discharge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTohaArN","text_ar":"اَطْهَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Msb.) And the pl. signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"days of a woman's state of pureness from the menstrual discharge."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n27216","headword_ar":"طَهِرٌ","root":"Thr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAhirN","text_ar":"طَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}